<!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"><title>Juno's 7 Mediterranean Journal</title><link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/css/style.css"></head><body><header class="hero"><div class="hero-inner"><p class="eyebrow">Summer 2026</p><h1>Juno's 7</h1><h2>Mediterranean Journal</h2><p class="lead" style="margin:auto">Cameron and Sophie’s first Mediterranean season working together, told through route, photographs, video and the small messages sent home.</p><nav class="nav"><a href="#latest">Latest</a><a href="voyage.html">Voyage So Far</a><a href="about.html">About Juno\'s 7</a><a href="crew.html">Meet the Crew</a><a href="#journal">Journal</a><a href="#gallery-section">Gallery</a><a href="#collector">Collector’s Edition</a></nav></div></header><section id="latest" class="section"><p class="kicker">Latest Entry</p><h2>Today in the journal</h2><div id="latestEntry"><article class="card at-sea"><div class="date">2026-06-30</div><h3>Underway — Changing Conditions</h3><p class="location">At Sea</p><blockquote class="quote">“Underway for another 2.5 hours.” / “A little stormy today.”</blockquote><p>The day began calm and later became stormier during the passage.</p></article></div></section><section class="section dark"><div class="wrap"><p class="kicker">Voyage Dashboard</p><h2>The route, live status and map</h2><p class="lead">The interactive route map lives on its own dashboard page, with satellite mapping, latest known position, tracker status and route timeline.</p><p><a class="button" href="voyage.html">Open Voyage Dashboard</a></p></div></section><section class="section"><p class="kicker">Latest Media</p><h2>Newest photos and videos</h2><div id="latestMedia" class="media-grid"></div></section><section id="journal" class="section"><p class="kicker">Journal</p><h2>Small moments</h2><div id="timeline" class="timeline"></div></section><section id="gallery-section" class="section"><p class="kicker">Archive</p><h2>Gallery</h2><div id="gallery" class="media-grid"></div></section><section id="collector" class="section dark"><div class="wrap"><p class="kicker">Collector’s Edition</p><h2>Printed keepsake direction</h2><div class="feature-grid"><article class="panel"><h3>Large photographs</h3><p>Designed for future coffee-table style pages.</p></article><article class="panel"><h3>Route and context</h3><p>Maps, places, dates and small comments preserved together.</p></article><article class="panel"><h3>Family archive</h3><p>Original media remains preserved while the website uses curated captions and journal entries.</p></article></div></div></section><footer class="footer"><p>Juno’s 7 Mediterranean Journal · Cameron & Sophie · Summer 2026</p></footer><script src="assets/js/app.js"></script></body></html>